Preparing the Environment to run terraform locally
Install terraform 1.9.7
Install terragrunt
Wsl version 1 should be configured 
Install wsl --set-default-version 1
      wsl --install -d Ubuntu
Install sops

Create a file in you wsl home:

$HOME/.terraformrc
provider_installation {
  network_mirror {
    url    = "https://prod.openstack.cadence.com:13808/v1/AUTH_b4e7f5d800c84ddbaf457388752738c2/terraform-providers/"
    include = ["registry.terraform.io/NetApp/*"]
  }
 
  direct {
    exclude = ["registry.terraform.io/NetApp/*"]
  }
 
}

Authentication Purposes 
https://statics.teams.cdn.office.net/evergreen-assets/safelinks/1/atp-safelinks.html
Go through this wiki for setting up cli
After this configure with your credentials
you should be able to run openstack commands

To run Terraform commands:
Mentioned profile AWS keys are required for exporting 
Github:
create a personal access token to configure with github and copy the key and save the key

From your wsl ubuntu you need to go to your project and able to run the terraform commands by going through all the above steps

